{"parentUuid":"55867a9d-d839-46fb-8248-7434dbf41df5","isSidechain":false,"attachment":{"type":"edited_text_file","filename":"/Users/alisha/Projects/skills/README.md","snippet":"1\t# Skills\n2\t\n3\tCross-agent skills and commands powered by Entire.\n4\t\n5\t## Skills\n6\t\n7\t### `session-handoff`\n8\t\n9\tReads Entire session metadata and helps move work from one agent to another without making the user reconstruct the context manually.\n10\t\n11\tCurrent behavior:\n12\t\n13\t- auto-detects the most recent session from `.git/entire-sessions/`\n14\t- reads the raw transcript at the path stored in session metadata\n15\t- produces a structured compaction summary (Task Overview, Current State, Important Discoveries, Next Steps, Context to Preserve) instead of dumping raw transcript lines\n16\t- surfaces unanswered questions from the previous agent for the user to answer\n17\t- supports checkpoint handoff via `entire explain --checkpoint <id> --full --no-pager`\n18\t- falls back to `entire explain --checkpoint <id> --raw-transcript --no-pager` if full output is unavailable\n19\t- resolves checkpoints from: local `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch, `.entire/settings.json` `checkpoint_remote`, or nearby local clone\n20\t- filters sessions by agent name (e.g. \"codex\", \"gemini\") when mentioned\n21\t\n22\t### `explain`\n23\t\n24\tTraces source code back to the original conversation where it was created. Use `/explain` with a function, file, or line of code to understand _why_ it exists.\n25\t\n26\tCurrent behavior:\n27\t\n28\t- identifies the commit that introduced the code via git blame/log\n29\t- reads the session transcript via `entire explain --no-pager --commit <sha>`\n30\t- works with functions, files, and individual line changes\n31\t- reports clearly when code is untracked, uncommitted, or created outside an Entire session\n32\t\n33\t### `search`\n34\t\n35\tSearches Entire checkpoint history and transcripts to find prior work by topic, repo, branch, author, or time window.\n36\t\n37\tCurrent behavior:\n38\t\n39\t- runs `entire search \"<query>\" --json` and summarizes the top matches\n40\t- supports filters: `--repo`, `--branch`, `--author`, `--date`, and inline query filters like `author:<name>`, `date:week`\n41\t- drills into a specific result with `entire explain --checkpoint <id> --full --no-pager`\n42\t- broadens searches progressively when initial results are empty (remove branch filter, widen date, simplify terms)\n43\t\n44\t## Installation\n45\t\n46\tInstall with [skills](https://skills.sh/) CLI (universal, works with any [Agent Skills](https://agentskills.io)-compatible tool):\n47\t\n48\t```bash\n49\tnpx skills add https://github.com/entireio/skills --all\n50\t# or a single skill:\n51\tnpx skills add https://github.com/entireio/skills --skill session-handoff\n52\t```\n53\t\n54\t<!-- prettier-ignore-start -->\n55\t\n56\t<details>\n57\t<summary>Claude Code</summary>\n58\t\n59\t```bash\n60\t/plugin marketplace add entireio/skills\n61\t/plugin install entire\n62\t```\n63\t\n64\t</details>\n65\t\n66\t<details>\n67\t<summary>Cursor</summary>\n68\t\n69\tCopy skills into the cross-client discovery directory:\n70\t\n71\t```bash\n72\tgit clone https://github.com/entireio/skills.git ~/.cursor/skills/entire\n73\t```\n74\t\n75\tCursor auto-discovers skills from `.agents/skills/` and `.cursor/skills/`.\n76\t\n77\t</details>\n78\t\n79\t<details>\n80\t<summary>Gemini CLI</summary>\n81\t\n82\t```bash\n83\tgemini extensions install https://github.com/entireio/skills\n84\t```\n85\t\n86\tUpdate with `gemini extensions update entire`.\n87\t\n88\t</details>\n89\t\n90\t<details>\n91\t<summary>OpenCode</summary>\n92\t\n93\tCopy skills into the cross-client discovery directory:\n94\t\n95\t```bash\n96\tgit clone https://github.com/entireio/skills.git ~/.agents/skills/entire\n97\t```\n98\t\n99\tOpenCode auto-discovers skills from `.agents/skills/`, `.opencode/skills/`, and `.claude/skills/`.\n100\t\n101\t</details>\n102\t\n103\t<details>\n104\t<summary>Codex (OpenAI)</summary>\n105\t\n106\tClone into the cross-client discovery path:\n107\t\n108\t```bash\n109\tgit clone https://github.com/entireio/skills.git ~/.agents/skills/entire\n110\t```\n111\t\n112\tCodex auto-discovers skills from `~/.agents/skills/` and `.agents/skills/`. Update with `cd ~/.agents/skills/entire && git pull`.\n113\t\n114\t</details>\n115\t\n116\t<details>\n117\t<summary>Copilot</summary>\n118\t\n119\t```bash\n120\t/plugin install https://github.com/entireio/skills\n121\t# or\n122\tgit clone https://github.com/entireio/skills.git ~/.copilot/skills/entire\n123\t```\n124\t\n125\tCopilot auto-discovers skills from `.copilot/skills/`.\n126\t\n127\t</details>\n128\t\n129\t<details>\n130\t<summary>Antigravity</summary>\n131\t\n132\tClone and symlink into the cross-client discovery path:\n133\t\n134\t```bash\n135\tgit clone https://github.com/entireio/skills.git ~/.antigravity/skills/entire\n136\t```\n137\t\n138\tUpdate with `cd ~/.antigravity/skills/entire && git pull`.\n139\t\n140\t</details>\n141\t\n142\t<!-- prettier-ignore-end -->\n143\t\n144\t## Quick Start\n145\t\n146\tNatural language examples:\n147\t\n148\t- \"hand off this session\"\n149\t- \"hand off the codex session\"\n150\t- \"pick up where codex left off\"\n151\t- \"hand off checkpoint 7b7c2be8a262\"\n152\t- `/explain parseConfig` — why does this function exist?\n153\t- `/explain src/auth.ts` — what drove this file's creation?\n154\t- \"search past work for rate limiting\"\n155\t- \"find checkpoints about the migration\"\n156\t- \"have we done this before?\"\n157\t\n158\t## Checkpoint Resolution\n159\t\n160\tCheckpoints are resolved in this order:\n161\t\n162\t1. local `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch\n163\t2. `.entire/settings.json` `checkpoint_remote`\n164\t3. nearby local clone"},"type":"attachment","uuid":"419172a0-7c59-42d4-add0-92320ea899e9","timestamp":"2026-04-24T17:17:40.240Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/alisha/Projects/skills","sessionId":"950